HEADWORD: infix notation
<hw>in"fix no*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>A notation for commands or instructions in
which the operator is inserted between the terms on which it operates.
Contrasted with <contr>prefix notation</contr> and <contr>postfix
notation</contr>.</def></p>

